97
00:06:00,333 --> 00:06:03,506
After that, no one dared mess with those two again.

98
00:06:05,243 --> 00:06:06,981
I didn’t want to mess with them.

99
00:06:06,981 --> 00:06:08,278
That’s why I walked away.

100
00:06:08,468 --> 00:06:10,646
Anyway, thank you for warning me.

101
00:06:15,881 --> 00:06:16,491
Wait.

102
00:06:34,597 --> 00:06:35,471
What?

103
00:06:38,606 --> 00:06:39,534
It was falling off.

104
00:07:12,840 --> 00:07:15,324
[Matthayom 6/1]

105
00:07:20,048 --> 00:07:21,286
Oh god.

106
00:07:21,720 --> 00:07:23,126
I’ll probably be late for homeroom.

107
00:07:25,542 --> 00:07:27,454
Hey, Ploypailin and Somsri!

108
00:07:27,454 --> 00:07:28,382
Get into the classroom.

109
00:07:28,382 --> 00:07:29,202
You’re late.

110
00:07:31,882 --> 00:07:32,508
Hi.

111
00:07:32,780 --> 00:07:33,409
Hi.

112
00:07:34,413 --> 00:07:37,754
Oh, you're Mok Diloksakulkan, right?

113
00:07:38,080 --> 00:07:38,748
Yes, I am.

114
00:07:39,752 --> 00:07:40,512
What are you doing?

115
00:07:41,028 --> 00:07:42,367
I’m on my way to the classroom.

116
00:07:42,503 --> 00:07:43,073
Let’s go.

117
00:07:43,073 --> 00:07:44,192
- Come on. Follow me.
- Okay.

118
00:07:48,378 --> 00:07:48,941
Oh.

119
00:07:48,941 --> 00:07:49,441
Yes?

120
00:07:50,011 --> 00:07:51,382
Let me tell your friends first.

121
00:07:51,626 --> 00:07:52,429
Wait here.

122
00:07:52,429 --> 00:07:53,355
Okay.

123
00:07:53,355 --> 00:07:54,523
Once I call you, you can come in.

124
00:07:54,731 --> 00:07:55,245
Okay.

125
00:07:55,245 --> 00:07:57,708
Also, don’t forget to take off your shoes, okay?

126
00:07:57,963 --> 00:07:58,850
Okay.

127
00:08:01,777 --> 00:08:05,759
Having fun chatting on the first day of your second semester?

128
00:08:07,119 --> 00:08:08,720
Okay, you’re all seated.

129
00:08:08,924 --> 00:08:10,218
Today is a good day.

130
00:08:10,566 --> 00:08:12,702
We’re going to have a new friend.

131
00:08:13,598 --> 00:08:14,336
Come on in.

132
00:08:16,317 --> 00:08:17,720
Give him a big hand.

133
00:08:20,432 --> 00:08:22,432
That must be the red hoodie guy from this morning.

134
00:08:22,432 --> 00:08:23,271
Yeah, it’s him.

135
00:08:23,271 --> 00:08:24,687
I can’t believe he’s in this class.

136
00:08:24,932 --> 00:08:26,932
Be nice to your friend.

137
00:08:27,130 --> 00:08:28,360
He just moved here from Bangkok.

138
00:08:28,663 --> 00:08:31,070
His name is Mok Diloksakulkan.

139
00:08:32,043 --> 00:08:34,043
I’d appreciate your advice. You can call me Moo.

140
00:08:40,811 --> 00:08:41,621
Don’t go yet.

141
00:08:41,621 --> 00:08:42,485
I’m not finished.

142
00:08:43,612 --> 00:08:46,280
If you know who Moo’s mom is, you’ll be chilled to the bone.

143
00:08:46,647 --> 00:08:48,538
She’s not a fan or an AC. Don’t make that joke.

144
00:08:49,849 --> 00:08:51,849
His mom is an alumna of this school

145
00:08:51,904 --> 00:08:56,510
and is now a producer at a music company with many famous songs.

146
00:08:56,510 --> 00:08:57,683
Don’t say a loudspeaker gets their songs heard.

147
00:08:57,849 --> 00:08:59,089
That joke is also outdated.

148
00:08:59,089 --> 00:09:01,412
This music company really has many famous songs.

149
00:09:02,018 --> 00:09:03,760
CP Entertainment.

150
00:09:04,298 --> 00:09:05,158
Have you heard of it?

151
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:18,379
If any of you want to be a singer, you can talk to Moo.

152
00:09:18,379 --> 00:09:19,092
Teacher.

153
00:09:19,092 --> 00:09:19,773
Right?

154
00:09:20,553 --> 00:09:21,316
Yes.

155
00:09:21,316 --> 00:09:22,933
Are you alright? You look a bit sheepish.

156
00:09:23,852 --> 00:09:26,015
Keep your spirits up. It’s your first morning here.

157
00:09:26,015 --> 00:09:26,883
Go to your seat.

158
00:09:31,042 --> 00:09:33,558
Alright, Let me do an attendance check.

159
00:09:35,349 --> 00:09:40,769
(Shit. They’re already giving me side-eyes on my first day.)

160
00:09:46,281 --> 00:09:48,000
Is this a lunch break?

161
00:10:14,526 --> 00:10:15,760
Hey, you!

162
00:10:19,313 --> 00:10:20,257
(Me?)

163
00:10:20,257 --> 00:10:21,520
Yes, you!

164
00:10:29,106 --> 00:10:30,129
Excuse me.

165
00:10:31,885 --> 00:10:33,523
Move!

166
00:10:33,659 --> 00:10:34,889
Let’s go!

167
00:10:48,444 --> 00:10:49,227
Shit, Kang!

168
00:10:49,471 --> 00:10:50,688
Why are you cursing at me?

169
00:10:50,688 --> 00:10:51,263
I’m not.

170
00:10:51,263 --> 00:10:51,975
I’m just shocked.

171
00:10:51,975 --> 00:10:52,571
What have you done?

172
00:10:52,571 --> 00:10:53,866
Why do you look like you’re running from ghosts?

173
00:10:53,866 --> 00:10:55,291
Ghosts would be less scary.

174
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:56,525
